{
  "texts": [
    "By using deep learning models that account for real-time data and personal preferences, this technology promises to revolutionize the way we interact with scents and flavors, creating products and services that are uniquely suited to individual needs.",
    "Although artificial intelligence has substantial potential to transform olfactory research, several unique challenges must be addressed to fully realize this potential.",
    "First, the quality and variability of olfactory sensor data present significant issues.",
    "Environmental factors, such as temperature fluctuations, humidity levels, and interference from other volatile compounds, often lead to inconsistencies in sensor outputs (Deshmukh et al. 2015).",
    "These variations complicate data interpretation and reduce the reliability of AI models trained on this information."
  ]
}